    "For our empirical analysis we generate predictions Ŷr = m(r;t) based on each bill's text description r by prompting GPT-4o (see Appendix Figure A12 for the specific prompt).",
    "Impressively, we find that GPT-4o correctly predicts the bill's outcome 91.2% of the time in the House and 92.5% of the time in the Senate (left panel of Table 1).",
    "Taking these results at face value, it would be tempting to conclude that GPT-4o is able to detect subtle undercurrents in the bill's writing that point the way the political winds are blowing.",
    "So what drives GPT-4o's ability to accurately predict whether a Congressional bill will pass the House or the Senate based only on its text description?",
    "The answer is that the the text of congressional legislation is likely included in GPT-4o's training dataset, producing training leakage in this prediction problem."
